&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory Clinical Physiologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;15 hours per week&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Maternity Leave Cover&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated individual to join the Physiological Measurements team to support the Trust wide Respiratory Physiology Service to a population of more than 440,000 people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role involves a high level of patient contact, working with all age groups, performing a variety of Respiratory investigations in our dedicated Lung function rooms based at DPOW and SGH –these tests include Full Pulmonary Function tests, with or without reversibility, Respiratory muscle function test, Flight Assessments, Field Exercise Tests, Arterial Blood Gases, Bronchial Challenge Tests and Sleep studies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A busy Inpatient and Outpatient Spirometry service is provided at DPOW and in the department, on the ward and 1 stop clinics in out-patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please see the accompanying job description and person specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For an informal discussion please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Jackie Carpus, Head of Medical Physics Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;03033 303816&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adele Hodson, Trust Clinical Lead Respiratory Physiologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;03033 304287&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
